(189, 'option_tree_settings', 'a:3:{s:15:\"contextual_help\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";a:22:{i:0;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"theme_install\";s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Installing the Theme\";s:7:\"content\";s:3328:\"After you have installed Wordpress, you have to install our Theme (Amory.zip). There are two ways of installing the Theme on your Wordpress:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>FTP Upload:</strong> Unzip the “Amory.zip” file and upload the contents into the /wp-content/themes folder on your server. If you get an error while activating the Theme uploaded via FTP, please ensure that <a href=\"http://premiumcoding.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/ftp-upload-opus.jpg\">transfer type is set to binary</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Wordpress Dashboard: </strong>Navigate to Appearance > Add New Themes >Upload. Go to browser, and select the zipped theme folder. Hit “Install Now” and the theme will be uploaded and installed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDownload the zipped theme pack to your local computer from themeforest and extract the ZIP file contents to a folder on your local computer. If you do not do that and install the first package directly you will get the following error:\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>The theme is missing the style.css stylesheet</strong>\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nSo be sure that you are always installin the file called <strong>\"AMORY.ZIP\"</strong>\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nOnce the theme is uploaded, you need to activate it. Go to Appearance > Themes and activate Amory Wordpress Theme. After the theme is activated, you need to install the required plugins for some extra functionality (Instagram, Contact Form and Shortcodes\r\n\r\nClick on begin installing plugins and you will be able to install all neccessary plugins. If you need them later on, you can find them in the Recommended plugins directory in the package you installed from Themeforest.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Instagram feed - this plugin adds the instagram gallery just above the footer. Instructions on how to connect to instagram are available in the plugin itself. Plugin can be downloaded from Wordpress repository at: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/instagram-feed/\">https://wordpress.org/plugins/instagram-feed</a></li>\r\n 	<li>Contact Form 7 - CONTACT FORM - this is a plugin that you will need of you want to add the contact form. Plugin can be downloaded from Wordpress repository at: <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/contact-form-7/\">http://wordpress.org/plugins/contact-form-7/</a></li>\r\n 	<li>Shortcodes Ultimate - this plugin adds the shortcodes. Plugin is not neccessary but if you wish to use some nice typography effects like dropcap, quotes and columns, you will have to install it. Plugin can be downloaded from Wordpress repository at: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/shortcodes-ultimate/\">https://wordpress.org/plugins/shortcodes-ultimate/</a></li>\r\n 	<li>Twitter Feed - this is a plugin that you will need of you want to add the twitter feed. Plugin can be downloaded from Wordpress repository at: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/recent-tweets-widget/\">https://wordpress.org/plugins/recent-tweets-widget/</a></li>\r\n 	<li>Facebook Feed - this is a plugin that you will need of you want to add the facebook feed. Plugin can be downloaded from Wordpress repository at: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/facebook-pagelike-widget/\">https://wordpress.org/plugins/facebook-pagelike-widget/</a></li>\r\n 	<li>Revolution Slider - can be found in the Recommended plugins directory in the files downloaded from Themeforest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2></h2>\";}i:1;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:16:\"how_to_set_amory\";s:5:\"title\";s:46:\"Demo Content - Theme looking like live preview\";s:7:\"content\";s:863:\"AUTO IMPORT - After theme installation go to theme options and click on the Import tab. Read the instructions carefully (we recommend to run it only on fresh Wordpress installation). If the auto import fails for some reason below are instructions for manual import.\r\n\r\nWe prepared a XML file for demo import. In this Theme we are not using pmc importer since the Theme is minimal and very simple. Please follow these steps:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Install the Amory WordPress Theme</li>\r\n 	<li>Import Demo content which is included with the Theme (in DEMO CONTENT directory)</li>\r\n 	<li>To use it, go to Tools > Import > WordPress and upload the xml file, choose to import everything, hit the button and wait.</li>\r\n 	<li>Set up the Home Page in Reading -> Settings</li>\r\n 	<li>You might also have to set Menus locations under Appearance -> Menu -> Menu Settings</li>\r\n</ul>\";}i:2;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:39:\"how_to_set_the_theme_like_live_previews\";s:5:\"title\";s:39:\"How to set the theme like live previews\";s:7:\"content\";s:648:\"For exact settings for all 6 live demos please check the other document included in the documentation, named: Amory-HOW-TO-SET-DEMOS\r\n<br><br>\r\nTIMEOUT ERROR\r\n<br><br>\r\nIf you get a timeout error while installing the demo content, you can contact your hosting provider and ask for a time increase (5 minutes should be enough on 99.9% of servers). Or you can follow the steps above and try to install the demo content manually. If you still have problems with installation, then please contact us via our support system at:  <a href=\"https://premiumcoding.com/wp-login.php?action=register\">https://premiumcoding.com/wp-login.php?action=register</a>\";}i:3;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"theme_s_options\";s:5:\"title\";s:15:\"Theme\'s Options\";s:7:\"content\";s:187:\"After activating the theme, you will notice that a new submenu item appeared under Appearance Tab called Theme\'s Options. To start customizing the Theme\'s settings click on Theme Options.\";}i:4;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:16:\"general_settings\";s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"General Settings\";s:7:\"content\";s:764:\"<strong>Logo, favicon and custom menus</strong> are set and added. Upload your logo, retina logo and custom logo for scroll if you need one (useful if you have transparent menu and need logos in different colors). You need to also upload a double sized logo for retina displays (be sure it is named like this Amory-logo1@2x.png with the @2x at the end).\r\n<br><br>\r\nEvery part / block of the home page can be enabled or disabled. This goes for the 3 posts under the logo, about us section and the instagram block.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>Responsive Mode</strong> can be disabled if you uncheck it.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>Smooth Scroll </strong>can be disabled if you uncheck it.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>Full width Page</strong> can be enabled or disabled (sidebar will be added).\";}i:5;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:18:\"home_page_settings\";s:5:\"title\";s:18:\"Home Page Settings\";s:7:\"content\";s:868:\"The content of the home page is set here. If you have checked all the blocks in the general settings, here is the place to add content to it.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>Uppper Block (three posts) - </strong>this is the part just below the logo. For each post you can upload the image and set title and url.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>About us Block - </strong>the about us section is very straightforward and simple. Add the image and content text (just like seen in our full width demo).\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>Quote Block - </strong>this is the text just above the footer. Simply add the text.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>Instagram block - </strong>simply add the title, your instagram username and link to your instagram profile. Detailed instructions on how to connect the plugin with your instagram account are available in the plugin itself at Settings - > Alpine:Instagram    -> General.\";}i:6;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"styling_options\";s:5:\"title\";s:15:\"Styling Options\";s:7:\"content\";s:778:\"<strong>Main Theme Color</strong> - color that is set throghout the Theme (red is default color for Amory Theme). Once you change the color please not that not all aspects of the site will change (some color will still be red). This is because on some parts of the Theme <strong>shortcodes</strong> are used. You need to change this manually as it gives you much more\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>freedom in color selection</strong> (it can be anything independant from theme\'s main color).\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<strong>Boxed version</strong> - if you need a boxed version, check it here and then set the background color or image.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>Custom Style</strong> - if you need to change CSS for certain parts of the Theme you can add it here (so you don’t have to edit the style.css).\";}i:7;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:9:\"typograhy\";s:5:\"title\";s:9:\"Typograhy\";s:7:\"content\";s:0:\"\";}i:8;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:45:\"social_options__error_page_and_footer_options\";s:5:\"title\";s:45:\"Social Options, Error Page and Footer Options\";s:7:\"content\";s:479:\"Last three tabs are very straightforward. In <strong>Social tab</strong> you can set your own social icons.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>Error Page</strong> defines the text on the <strong>404 page not found. </strong>This page appears everytime a user misclicks or comes to a page that does not exist.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>Footer Options</strong> set the text that is found at the very bottom of the Theme (below the footer part with widgets). Usually copyright information is entered here.\";}i:9;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:25:\"setting__up_the_home_page\";s:5:\"title\";s:25:\"Setting  up the Home Page\";s:7:\"content\";s:738:\"After you decide what page do you want to use, go to <strong>Settings > Reading</strong> and in the Front page displays choose a static page, then select your just created page. After this, you should change the <strong>Blog pages</strong> show at most value from 10 to 3 posts (for the same appearance as in our live demo). This theme works best with this setup. Hit “Save Changes” and you’re done.\r\n<br><br>\r\nNext, you should setup your <strong>permalinks </strong>to look pretty. Please go to Settings > Permalinks, choose the Custom Structure, and use this: /%category%/%postname%/\r\n<br><br>\r\n<a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Using_Permalinks#Permalinks_without_mod_rewrite\">READ THIS</a> about permalinks on Windows Servers!\";}i:10;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:28:\"navigation_and_menu_settings\";s:5:\"title\";s:28:\"Navigation and Menu Settings\";s:7:\"content\";s:389:\"The last step before you can start working with the new theme is to create your menu. Go to Appearance > Menus and you will see a panel where you can create new menus. Create one, add your created pages to it (from the left side panels) and save it. Now set the locations for the menu that you just created. The main menu will probably be set at Main Menu, Responsive Menu and Scroll Menu.\";}i:11;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:21:\"customizing_menu_item\";s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"Customizing Menu Item\";s:7:\"content\";s:649:\"<strong>The Navigation Label</strong> – this field specifies the title of the item on your custom menu. This is what your visitors will see when they visit your site/blog.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>The Title Attribute</strong> – this field specifies the Alternative (‘Alt’) text for the menu item. This text will be displayed when a user’s mouse hovers over a menu item.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Click on the arrow in the top right-hand corner of the menu item to expand it.</li>\r\n 	<li>Enter the values for the Navigation Label and Title Attribute that you want to assign to the item.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click the Save Menu button to save your changes.</li>\r\n</ul>\";}i:12;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:26:\"creating_multi_level_menus\";s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Creating Multi Level Menus\";s:7:\"content\";s:1563:\"When planning the structure of your menu, it helps to think of each menu item as a heading in a formal report document. In a formal report, main section headings (Level 1 headings) are the nearest to the left of the page; sub-section headings (Level 2 headings) are indented slightly further to the right; any other subordinate headings (Level 3, 4, etc) within the same section are indented even further to the right.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe WordPress menu editor allows you to create multi-level menus using a simple ‘drag and drop’ interface. Drag menu items up or down to change their order of appearance in the menu. Drag menu items left or right in order to create sub-levels within your menu.\r\n<br><br>\r\nTo make one menu item a subordinate of another, you need to position the ‘child’ underneath its ‘parent’ and then drag it slightly to the right.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>How to position the sub-menu item</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Position the mouse over the ‘child’ menu item.</li>\r\n 	<li>Whilst holding the left mouse button, drag it to the right.</li>\r\n 	<li>Release the mouse button.</li>\r\n 	<li>Repeat these steps for each sub-menu item.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click the Save Menu button in the Menu Editor to save your changes.</li>\r\n 	<li>Select the Pages that you want to add by clicking the checkbox next to each Page’s title.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click the Add <strong>to Menu button</strong> located at the bottom of this pane to add your selection(s) to the menu that you created in the previous step.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click the <strong>Save Menu</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\";}i:13;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:18:\"deleting_menu_item\";s:5:\"title\";s:18:\"Deleting Menu Item\";s:7:\"content\";s:340:\"<ul>\r\n 	<li>Locate the menu item that you want to remove in the menu editor window</li>\r\n 	<li>Click on the arrow icon in the top right-hand corner of the menu item/box to expand it.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click on the Remove link. The menu item/box will be immediately removed.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click the Save Menu button to save your changes.</li>\r\n</ul>\";}i:14;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"adding_posts\";s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Adding Posts\";s:7:\"content\";s:967:\"These are the default steps that you need to do in order to add a blog post:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Go to Posts > Add New</li>\r\n 	<li>Enter a title and some content.</li>\r\n 	<li>Select a post category.</li>\r\n 	<li>Add some relevant tags.</li>\r\n 	<li>Choose a post format from the right. There are a few types of custom formats that can be used (Standard, Link, Gallery, Video, Audio).</li>\r\n 	<li>Setup the content of the post format(either a gallery, a link, an image, aquote, an mp3 or a video).</li>\r\n 	<li>Insert all of your remaining content in the content area. You can have images, paragraphs, etc.</li>\r\n 	<li>Write a few words excerpt(it is good for search results and SEO to have an excerpt, no matter what kind of content do you have in your post).</li>\r\n 	<li>Hit “Publish” and you’re all done.</li>\r\n</ul><br><br>\r\n<strong>Recommended size</strong> of Post\'s featured image is 1160 x 770 for the full width version and 760 x 500 for the version with sidebar.\";}i:15;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"adding_pages\";s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Adding Pages\";s:7:\"content\";s:464:\"<ul>\r\n 	<li>Go to Pages > Add New</li>\r\n 	<li>Enter a title and some content.</li>\r\n 	<li>Select a page template or leave the default(more on this just after).</li>\r\n 	<li>Select a layout for the page. Each page can have a custom sidebar or not.</li>\r\n 	<li>Write a few words excerpt(it is good for search results and SEO to have an excerpt, no matter what kind of content do you have in your page).</li>\r\n 	<li>Hit “Publish” and you’re all done.</li>\r\n</ul>\";}i:16;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:23:\"recommended_image_sizes\";s:5:\"title\";s:23:\"Recommended image sizes\";s:7:\"content\";s:159:\"<ul>\r\n 	<li>Blog 1160 x 770 (fullwidth), 760 x 500 (with sidebar)</li>\r\n 	<li>Upper three posts - 640 x 400</li>\r\n 	<li>About us avatar - 300 x 300</li>\r\n</ul>\";}i:17;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:11:\"child_theme\";s:5:\"title\";s:11:\"Child Theme\";s:7:\"content\";s:591:\"A WordPress child theme is a theme that inherits the functionality of another\r\n<br><br>\r\ntheme, called the parent theme. Child theme allows you to modify, or add to the\r\n<br><br>\r\nfunctionality of that parent theme. Instead of modifying the theme files directly, you can create a child theme and override within.\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\nYou will find child Theme version in the package you downloaded from Themeforest in the directory called CHILD-THEME.\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nMore information about Wordpress child themes can be found on <a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Child_Themes\">Wordpress Codex.</a>\";}i:18;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:11:\"seo_advices\";s:5:\"title\";s:11:\"SEO Advices\";s:7:\"content\";s:714:\"The theme is built in a way to be SEO friendly, by emphasizing titles with heading tags, having the content before anything else, stripping out useless content, fast loading, setting titles in the header for better crawling, etc.. But you have to remember that Content is King! So you shouldn’t blame the theme because your website doesn’t appear in search engines. You should always focus on providing good content and in this way, your website will definitely look great in search engines. Also, you should always install a popular SEO plugin which will make the most of keywords and descriptions.\r\n<br><br>\r\nWe recommend using the <a href=\"https://yoast.com/wordpress/plugins/seo/\">Yoast Plugin for SEO</a>.\";}i:19;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:47:\"what_to_do_if_i_get_error_upon_theme_activation\";s:5:\"title\";s:47:\"What to do if I get error upon Theme Activation\";s:7:\"content\";s:439:\"If you receive the following error:\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>Parse error: syntax error, unexpected $end in …/wp-content/themes/Amory/admin/theme-options.php on line 1</strong>\r\n<br><br>\r\nThis happens if you install the Theme via FTP and the transfer type is not set to <strong>binary</strong>. So set the transfer type to binary as can be <a href=\"http://premiumcoding.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/ftp-upload-opus.jpg\">seen on this link</a>.\";}i:20;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:36:\"how_to_change_croping_size_of_images\";s:5:\"title\";s:36:\"How to change croping size of images\";s:7:\"content\";s:653:\"Amory uses several different image sizes which are listed below:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Blog 1160 x 770 (fullwidth), 760 x 500 (with sidebar)</li>\r\n 	<li>Upper three posts - 640 x 400</li>\r\n 	<li>About us avatar - 300 x 300</li>\r\n</ul><br><br>\r\nThese are the general sizes used. Different sections of the Theme uses different croping. To change it, open functions.php and at the top you will notice code like:\r\n<br><br>\r\n<strong>add_image_size( \'blog\', 1160, 770, true );</strong>\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nAfter you change the size of the image, you need to <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/regenerate-thumbnails/\">regenerate Thumbs</a> for the changes to be visible.\";}i:21;a:3:{s:2:\"id\";s:33:\"how_to_properly_set_up_video_post\";s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"How to update your Theme\";s:7:\"content\";s:576:\"Below is a short guide of how to update your Theme.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>First and best practice is to <strong>make a backup</strong>, download your current theme to your desktop via ftp. After that delete theme from WordPress.</li>\r\n 	<li>Go to themeforest, to your downloads page, this link precisely: <strong>http://themeforest.net/downloads</strong> and download Amory theme</li>\r\n 	<li>Upload the new version of theme <strong>via your WordPress dashboard</strong> or via ftp and that\'s it.</li>\r\n 	<li>Add widgets block to where you would like to have the search bar.</li>\r\n</ul>\";}}s:7:\"sidebar\";s:665:\"Typograhy is an important aspect of any blog Theme. You can add any font from <a href=\"https://fonts.google.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><b>Google Web font</b></a>library. First you need to add fonts that you wish to use in different parts of the theme (headings, body and menu). Default fonts will be loaded according to the layout you choose at the start.\r\n\r\nClick on Add Google Font button and select the desired font from the drop-down menu. Set all variations of the font that you need (regular, italic, latin,...). Numbers from 100 to 900 means how bold the font is, so 100 is extra thin and 900 is extra bold. Please note that not all the fonts have all variations.\";}s:8:\"sections\";a:18:{i:0;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:7:\"fa-cogs\";s:2:\"id\";s:7:\"general\";s:5:\"title\";s:7:\"General\";}i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:8:\"fa-cubes\";s:2:\"id\";s:4:\"logo\";s:5:\"title\";s:4:\"Logo\";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:10:\"fa-sliders\";s:2:\"id\";s:27:\"home_page_revolution_slider\";s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"Revolution slider\";}i:3;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:18:\"fa-shopping-basket\";s:2:\"id\";s:11:\"woocommerce\";s:5:\"title\";s:11:\"WooCommerce\";}i:4;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:8:\"fa-inbox\";s:2:\"id\";s:8:\"post_box\";s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"Featured Posts\";}i:5;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:8:\"fa-clone\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"about_us_block\";s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"About us block\";}i:6;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:12:\"fa-instagram\";s:2:\"id\";s:15:\"instagram_block\";s:5:\"title\";s:15:\"Instagram block\";}i:7;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:9:\"fa-pencil\";s:2:\"id\";s:10:\"blog_pages\";s:5:\"title\";s:10:\"Blog pages\";}i:8;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:9:\"fa-eraser\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"styling_otions\";s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"Style Your Theme\";}i:9;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:7:\"fa-css3\";s:2:\"id\";s:12:\"custom_style\";s:5:\"title\";s:10:\"Custom CSS\";}i:10;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:9:\"fa-flickr\";s:2:\"id\";s:19:\"custom_javascript_h\";s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"Custom JavaScript\";}i:11;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:7:\"fa-font\";s:2:\"id\";s:10:\"typography\";s:5:\"title\";s:10:\"Typography\";}i:12;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:17:\"fa-connectdevelop\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"social_options\";s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Social icons\";}i:13;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:9:\"fa-folder\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"404_error_page\";s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"404 Error page\";}i:14;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:11:\"fa-download\";s:2:\"id\";s:14:\"footer_options\";s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Footer\";}i:15;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:9:\"fa-server\";s:2:\"id\";s:21:\"simple_layout_builder\";s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Mini Builder\";}i:16;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:10:\"fa-support\";s:2:\"id\";s:7:\"support\";s:5:\"title\";s:7:\"Support\";}i:17;a:3:{s:4:\"font\";s:9:\